Her name is Baby Thando and she is no ordinary doll.She speaks 25 phrases in Zulu and 25 phrases in English. Baby Thando is an educational doll that talks back to you
at a push of a button on her belly.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>She speaks phrases such as “Bheka mama ilanga libalele”
(Look Mommy the sun is shining) and “Cela ungixoxela inganekwane” (Please tell
me a story).Sphe Zikode – Brand Manager for Prima Toys was quoted
saying the fact that she also has an educational aspect is a huge plus for both
parents and children. "She is the perfect companion for children who want
to learn English, a language which is not their mother tongue. Thando also
provides the opportunity for children to start speaking Zulu or add to their
vocabulary.” Baby Thando is a baby doll designed specifically for
little girls in South Africa and is set to pave the way for a new generation of
dolls.Playing is essential for cognitive as well as fine and
gross motor skill development. Through play, children get to develop these
motor skills and practise language. “With Baby Thando, children have the added benefit of
learning a new language and words,” said Sphe. Additionally, playing with dolls provides the opportunity
for children to understand new learning concepts and develop imaginative play
skills.